ling exponents $\\zeta(n)$\n(resp. singularity spectrum $D(h)$) agree very well with a lognormal model with\nan intermittent parameter $\\mu=0.33$. Due to large-scale effects, the results\nprovided by the SFs are biased.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Feb 2014 12:48:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
